org.jlokalize
Class LanguageTreeManager

java.lang.Object
  org.jlokalize.LanguageTreeManager

public class LanguageTreeManager
extends java.lang.Object

Helper utilities for handling trees composed of TreeNodes. - Insertion in the tree according to a language, country, variant hierarchy including nodes in between. - Removing nodes from the tree. - Sorting children in the tree. - Getting, setting Master nodes in the tree

Method Detail

insertLangPropInTree

public static org.tools.common.TreeNode<LanguageProperties> insertLangPropInTree(org.tools.common.TreeNode<LanguageProperties> root,
                                                                                 LanguageProperties lang)
Automatically inserts a new LanguageProperty as a node in the tree at the right place and inserts any missing nodes in between, so even a new root is created if no root was given before. The position is specified by the combination of language, country and variant tag. The base is either taken from root or if there is no root then it is taken from the parameter. The clear name is set for all created nodes. Comment: Already existing nodes with the same properties are replaced by the new LanguageProperty. Comment: The inserting in a children list of nodes is not sorted.

Parameters:
root -
lang -
Returns:
The new root, in case it has changed.

removeNodeFromTree

public static boolean removeNodeFromTree(org.tools.common.TreeNode<LanguageProperties> node)
Removes a node from the tree, if it isn't the root and hasn't any children. Otherwise only the keys are deleted.

Parameters:
node - The node to remove.
Returns:
True if the whole node could be deleted, false otherwise.

setClearNamesInTree

public static void setClearNamesInTree(org.tools.common.TreeNode<LanguageProperties> root)
